Hi all,
I am writing a class that inherits from UserSolutionObject. However, I am running into registration errors that I have yet to encounter when inheriting from other MOOSE classes.
I am trying to incorporate into this class ComputeDeformationGradient the ability to read a user solution object directly. However, the issue does not seem to stem from how I implement the functions from UserSolutionObject but rather something odd with the class registration.
I am emphasizing the UserSolutionObject as this class compiled fine before I changed it to inherit from UserSolutionObject
The error in question:

I'll provide abbreviated versions of my code
Here is the initialization code for my .C file
#include "ADRankTwoTensorForward.h"
#include "ComputeDeformationGradient.h"
#include "Material.h"
#include "libmesh/point.h"

registerADMooseObject("raccoonApp", ComputeDeformationGradient);

InputParameters
ComputeDeformationGradient::validParams()
{
  InputParameters params = Material::validParams();
  params += BaseNameInterface::validParams();
  params += SolutionUserObject::validParams();

  params.addClassDescription(
      "This class computes the deformation gradient. Eigen deformation gradients are extracted "
      "from the total deformation gradient. The F-bar approach can optionally be used to correct "
      "volumetric locking.");

      //rest of params

  return params;
}

ComputeDeformationGradient::ComputeDeformationGradient(const InputParameters & parameters)
  : Material(parameters),
    BaseNameInterface(parameters),
    SolutionUserObject(parameters),
   //Other variable initializations 
{
  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < _Fgs.size(); ++i)
    _Fgs[i] = &Material::getADMaterialProperty<RankTwoTensor>(_Fg_names[i]);

  if (MaterialBase::getParam<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
    MaterialBase::paramError("use_displaced_mesh",
                             "The strain calculator needs to run on the undisplaced mesh.");
}

//Function Definitions

And here is my header file
